summary.para: Defines the ControlProperties Class.
This class is available in Office 2010 and above.
When the object is serialized out as xml, it's qualified name is x:controlPr.

remarks.format:
## Remarks [!INCLUDE[openxmlnoticeiso](~/includes/openxmlnoticeiso.md)]
**controlPr (Embedded Control Properties)**
This element specifies the visual, positional and cell linkage properties of an embedded control.
[*Example*: The following example demonstrates an non-printing embedded control linked to cell A4 that is represented as an image:
```xml <controls> <control … > <controlPr print="false" autoLine="false" linkedCell="$A$4" cf="pict" r:id="rId5"> <anchor sizeWithCells="true"> <from> … </from> <to> … </to> </anchor> </controlPr> </control> </controls> ```
*end example*]
|Parent Elements| |---------------------| |control (§18.3.1.19)|
|Child Elements|Subclause| |--------------------|---------------| |anchor (Object Cell Anchor)|§18.3.1.1|
[*Note*: The W3C XML Schema definition of this element’s content model (CT_ControlPr) is located in §A.2. *end note*]
[!INCLUDE[openxmlnoticeiso](~/includes/openxmlcopyrightiso.md)]
